Find your happiness

13
00:01:14,026 --> 00:01:19,026
Come back again

14
00:01:20,218 --> 00:01:28,218
Do you remember? Heidi had secretly sneaked away to look at the mountains from a
high church tower.

15
00:01:28,218 --> 00:01:34,218
But all she saw were houses, stones and, far behind, the Main.

16
00:01:34,218 --> 00:01:42,218
She had climbed up the stairs to the observation deck with so much hope, but on
the way down she was sad and disappointed.

17
00:01:42,218 --> 00:01:49,218
The tower guard tried to encourage her, but what did he know about Heimweh?

18
00:01:50,218 --> 00:01:56,218
Here's what he told us.

19
00:01:56,538 --> 00:01:59,538
I'm tired. I can't walk anymore.

20
00:02:21,242 --> 00:02:23,242
Hush, be quiet.

21
00:02:26,242 --> 00:02:28,242
Little kitten.

22
00:02:30,242 --> 00:02:32,242
Well, do you like the kittens?

23
00:02:32,242 --> 00:02:34,242
I once had a dog and two goats.

24
00:02:34,242 --> 00:02:36,242
Josef, Schweli and Berli.

25
00:02:38,242 --> 00:02:40,242
Why don't you take one?

26
00:02:42,242 --> 00:02:44,242
May I keep a kitten?

27
00:02:44,242 --> 00:02:45,242
Of course.

28
00:02:46,242 --> 00:02:48,242
Thank you, I'll pick one, okay?

29
00:02:51,242 --> 00:02:52,090
You're welcome.

30
00:02:52,090 --> 00:02:54,090
You go out nicely.

31
00:02:56,090 --> 00:02:58,090
Off with you.

32
00:02:58,090 --> 00:03:01,090
Of course she doesn't want to give them away.

33
00:03:01,090 --> 00:03:02,090
Cats.

34
00:03:02,090 --> 00:03:04,090
Does it matter which one I take?

35
00:03:04,090 --> 00:03:07,090
Or is there one that you would like to keep for yourself?

36
00:03:07,090 --> 00:03:08,090
I'll eat it right away.

37
00:03:08,090 --> 00:03:11,090
No, I'll take the dark one.

38
00:03:11,090 --> 00:03:13,090
Or the white one.

39
00:03:13,090 --> 00:03:15,026
Or...

40
00:03:15,026 --> 00:03:17,026
...this one.

41
00:03:17,026 --> 00:03:19,026
From here you can have them all.

42
00:03:19,026 --> 00:03:22,026
I have to see how I'm going to get rid of them anyway.

43
00:03:24,026 --> 00:03:26,026
Do you know the house of Sesemanns?

44
00:03:26,026 --> 00:03:28,026
Everyone in town knows the house.

45
00:03:28,026 --> 00:03:30,026
Then bring the cats there.

46
00:03:30,026 --> 00:03:32,026
The house is so big, everyone fits in there.

47
00:03:33,026 --> 00:03:34,026
Stop!

48
00:03:35,026 --> 00:03:37,026
Children and little animals.

49
00:03:38,604 --> 00:03:42,604
Little white kittens have white tits.

50
00:03:42,604 --> 00:03:44,604
My kitten is so cute.

51
00:03:50,764 --> 00:03:52,764
Let's go on.

52
00:04:08,076 --> 00:04:11,076
This is the house of Sesemanns. We have finally arrived.

53
00:04:11,076 --> 00:04:14,076
Goodbye! Don't forget the money!

54
00:04:14,076 --> 00:04:16,076
No, but wait a moment!

55
00:04:24,300 --> 00:04:27,300
The whole house is in bright excitement. Quick!

56
00:04:27,300 --> 00:04:29,300
Hey, open the door!

57
00:04:30,300 --> 00:04:32,300
I should climb up to the church tower.

58
00:04:32,300 --> 00:04:37,300
Oh dear heaven, if you tell the old scarecrow that I brought you up to the idea,
I will be relieved.

59
00:04:37,300 --> 00:04:39,300
That fits, scarecrow fits.

60
00:04:39,300 --> 00:04:41,300
For God's sake, don't call her that.

61
00:04:42,300 --> 00:04:44,300
Is that a cat or am I dreaming?

62
00:04:44,300 --> 00:04:48,300
I completely forgot. What am I doing now? How do I hide the cat in front of Mrs.
Rottenmeier?

63
00:04:53,036 --> 00:04:56,036
Come in.

64
00:04:56,036 --> 00:04:58,036
Good evening.

65
00:04:58,036 --> 00:05:00,036
Oh, Heidi.

66
00:05:00,036 --> 00:05:03,036
I want to apologize, I'm late.

67
00:05:03,036 --> 00:05:06,036
I know that by myself that you're late.

68
00:05:06,036 --> 00:05:10,036
I didn't have to tell you that leaving the house is a bad habit

69
00:05:10,036 --> 00:05:12,036
and no one to tell you anything about it.

70
00:05:12,036 --> 00:05:17,036
And if you go out in the future, I would like to ask you to be back on time for
the meals.

71
00:05:17,036 --> 00:05:20,036
I don't want to upset my nerves today.

72
00:05:20,754 --> 00:05:22,754
It would make no sense.

73
00:05:22,754 --> 00:05:24,754
You always notice that you don't...

74
00:05:24,754 --> 00:05:26,754
Oh!

75
00:05:26,754 --> 00:05:28,754
Adelheid,

76
00:05:28,754 --> 00:05:30,754
if you intend to make fun of me,

77
00:05:30,754 --> 00:05:32,754
then do it upstairs in your room.

78
00:05:32,754 --> 00:05:34,754
I don't want to. I mean, I can't.

79
00:05:34,754 --> 00:05:36,754
I...

80
00:05:36,754 --> 00:05:38,754
There it is again.

81
00:05:38,754 --> 00:05:40,754
Adelheid, go to your room.

82
00:05:40,754 --> 00:05:42,754
But why?

83
00:05:42,754 --> 00:05:44,754
Now I've had enough.

84
00:05:44,754 --> 00:05:46,754
I'm at the end of my nerve power.

85
00:05:46,754 --> 00:05:48,754
Disappear

86
00:05:48,754 --> 00:05:49,922
and off to bed!

87
00:05:49,922 --> 00:05:51,022
...without dinner!

88
00:05:51,022 --> 00:05:53,722
I'm definitely not following her, Miss Rottenmeier.

89
00:05:53,722 --> 00:05:55,422
It's a real cat.

90
00:05:57,922 --> 00:05:59,822
She's very small and cute.

91
00:05:59,822 --> 00:06:00,522
Help!

92
00:06:01,122 --> 00:06:02,022
Tinette!

93
00:06:02,322 --> 00:06:03,522
Tinette!

94
00:06:04,522 --> 00:06:05,622
You thief!

95
00:06:06,122 --> 00:06:07,522
Cameraman!

96
00:06:08,022 --> 00:06:08,922
You thief!

97
00:06:10,822 --> 00:06:12,322
Tinette! Sebastian!

98
00:06:12,322 --> 00:06:13,922
Get out of here!

99
00:06:15,922 --> 00:06:17,222
She has a very soft...

100
00:06:17,278 --> 00:06:19,278
Don't be afraid, Phil.

101
00:06:21,278 --> 00:06:23,278
I've never pet an animal before.

102
00:06:23,278 --> 00:06:25,278
Oh, she's as light as a feather.

103
00:06:25,278 --> 00:06:27,278
She can't move at all.

104
00:06:27,278 --> 00:06:29,278
I almost can't feel her. How cute!

105
00:06:31,278 --> 00:06:33,278
How are you, little cat?

106
00:06:33,278 --> 00:06:35,278
Mrs. Quirter.

107
00:06:35,278 --> 00:06:37,278
I'm going to tell Mrs. Rottenmeier

108
00:06:37,278 --> 00:06:39,278
that she can't take part in dinner

109
00:06:39,278 --> 00:06:41,278
and that she wants to start without you.

110
00:06:41,278 --> 00:06:45,278
And I'm going to take care of the cat.

111
00:06:45,396 --> 00:06:47,396
It's my cat. Did you chase it away?

112
00:06:47,396 --> 00:06:49,396
Order from Mrs. Rottenmeier.

113
00:06:49,396 --> 00:06:51,396
The cat stays. She didn't do anything to anyone.

114
00:06:51,396 --> 00:06:54,396
She's small. Without our help, she can't find anything to eat and is starving.

115
00:06:54,396 --> 00:06:57,396
It can't be changed. Mrs. Rottenmeier wants it.

116
00:07:01,278 --> 00:07:04,278
I know what. We'll just bring her up into the tower room.

117
00:07:04,278 --> 00:07:06,278
She'll never dare to go in front of a rotten man.

118
00:07:06,278 --> 00:07:08,278
Oh, yes, we'll do that. That would be great.

119
00:07:08,278 --> 00:07:10,278
Fantastic. A fantastic...

120
00:07:10,278 --> 00:07:14,278
And you, Sebastian, you'll make a warm place up there so she won't be afraid.

121
00:07:14,278 --> 00:07:16,278
She means... she means...

122
00:07:16,278 --> 00:07:18,278
Oh, please, Sebastian, please.

123
00:07:18,278 --> 00:07:22,278
Well, well, well. If you ask me like that, then I can't help it, can I?

124
00:07:22,278 --> 00:07:24,278
Hooray!

