Adelheid, in the house of Sesemann it is an unwritten law that you enter the
breakfast room at 8.05 a.m. and not a minute later. Do you understand me?

195
00:12:08,234 --> 00:12:09,234
Yes.

196
00:12:09,234 --> 00:12:14,234
And put your hands on the table as it should be. What did you do to your face,
scratcher?

197
00:12:14,234 --> 00:12:22,234
That? I don't know. I fell out of bed this morning and scratched myself.

198
00:12:23,234 --> 00:12:25,234
That doesn't hurt, that heals quickly.

199
00:12:28,792 --> 00:12:31,992
Take your fingers off the wound. Tinette, get something to disinfect.

200
00:12:31,992 --> 00:12:32,992
Yes.

201
00:12:33,992 --> 00:12:36,992
She doesn't need that. A spit is the best thing to do.

202
00:12:36,992 --> 00:12:40,492
Tinette, please do what I've just told you to do.

203
00:12:40,492 --> 00:12:42,492
You'd better take her out with you right away.

204
00:12:42,492 --> 00:12:44,492
Yes, madam. Come on.

205
00:12:46,992 --> 00:12:50,092
And you'd better give her some anti-fever drops right away.

206
00:12:50,092 --> 00:12:52,292
Yes, I'll do that right away, madam.

207
00:12:53,292 --> 00:12:56,792
Are all the children who grew up in the mountains so careless?

208
00:12:56,968 --> 00:12:59,968
What are we going to do with the child?

209
00:13:11,074 --> 00:13:14,074
Yes, I'll be right there.

210
00:13:16,074 --> 00:13:18,074
One moment, I'm coming.

211
00:13:21,074 --> 00:13:24,074
Oh, what do you want here with us?

212
00:13:24,074 --> 00:13:25,074
Good day.

213
00:13:25,074 --> 00:13:28,074
Aha, I understand, but I can tell you that.

214
00:13:28,074 --> 00:13:30,074
Bed and rest is forbidden in this house.

215
00:13:30,074 --> 00:13:32,074
So make sure you get out of here, get out of here.

216
00:13:32,074 --> 00:13:34,074
Does a little girl live here?

217
00:13:34,074 --> 00:13:36,074
Two little girls live here.

218
00:13:36,074 --> 00:13:37,074
Is one of the two Heidi?

219
00:13:37,074 --> 00:13:39,074
Has she done something again?

220
00:13:39,208 --> 00:13:42,208
So she lives here. I brought her here yesterday.

221
00:13:42,208 --> 00:13:45,208
Then you just brought her here. And now watch out that you get away,

222
00:13:45,208 --> 00:13:47,208
otherwise I'll forget and then it'll be terrible.

223
00:13:47,208 --> 00:13:51,208
I'll get 20 pfennigs from her. She met me on the street yesterday

224
00:13:51,208 --> 00:13:54,208
and promised the money when I showed her a high church tower.

225
00:13:54,208 --> 00:13:55,208
And I did that too.

226
00:13:55,208 --> 00:13:56,208
So, so, 20 pfennigs.

227
00:13:56,208 --> 00:14:00,208
Showing a high tower, met on the street yesterday.

228
00:14:06,050 --> 00:14:09,650
Well, then come on in, maybe we can do something for you.

229
00:14:09,650 --> 00:14:10,650
Come on, Augustin.

230
00:14:17,570 --> 00:14:23,570
Wait here for me and be quiet. I will now call you to Miss Clara.

231
00:14:23,570 --> 00:14:28,570
And as soon as I ask you to come in, you start playing the organ, understood?

232
00:14:28,570 --> 00:14:32,570
What do you think she will be happy about?

233
00:14:35,570 --> 00:14:37,570
Yes, come in.

234
00:14:38,570 --> 00:14:45,160
I regret many times that I have to interrupt the class, but a boy has just come
and wishes to speak to the Blessed Miss.

235
00:14:45,160 --> 00:14:47,160
Oh, I'm getting a visitor. Yes, who is it?

236
00:14:47,160 --> 00:14:49,160
It's a stranger.

237
00:14:52,160 --> 00:14:54,160
Let him come in.

238
00:14:54,160 --> 00:14:55,160
Gladly.

239
00:14:55,160 --> 00:14:58,160
Miss Clara, I have to protest. We can't interrupt the class.

240
00:14:58,160 --> 00:15:02,160
But why not? Now someone has come for the first time and wants to speak to me.

241
00:15:02,160 --> 00:15:04,160
I've never had a visitor before.

242
00:15:04,160 --> 00:15:09,160
Well, but just for a moment. Let him come in, okay?

243
00:15:11,002 --> 00:15:16,002
You may come in now, and don't forget to play on your organ right away.

244
00:15:16,002 --> 00:15:18,002
Come on, Augustin.

245
00:15:32,308 --> 00:15:35,308
What do you mean? Do you want to stop?

246
00:15:35,308 --> 00:15:37,308
But why? It's beautiful!

247
00:15:37,308 --> 00:15:39,308
That should be beautiful? That?

248
00:15:53,308 --> 00:15:56,084
It's nice that you came, little boy.

249
00:15:56,084 --> 00:15:58,084
Oh, you know the boy?

250
00:15:58,084 --> 00:16:00,084
Yes, I met him yesterday in town.

251
00:16:00,084 --> 00:16:02,084
He showed me the way to the church tower.

252
00:16:03,084 --> 00:16:05,084
Do you have time? Can you play something for me?

253
00:16:05,084 --> 00:16:06,084
Yes!

254
00:16:06,084 --> 00:16:07,084
Please play.

255
00:16:16,020 --> 00:16:18,020
Clara, look at his feet!

256
00:16:29,908 --> 00:16:34,908
What music? There's no music on the timetable for today.

257
00:16:34,908 --> 00:16:36,908
And such an ordinary music.

258
00:16:36,908 --> 00:16:38,908
That's what she's up to.

259
00:16:38,908 --> 00:16:42,908
At this point, stop with the noise. Stop that you come out. Leave the house
immediately.

260
00:16:50,908 --> 00:16:53,300
Bring this dragon out of the house immediately.

261
00:16:53,300 --> 00:16:55,300
She's a beautiful girl, don't worry about it.

262
00:16:56,300 --> 00:16:58,300
Ah, Sebastian! Ah, Sebastian!

263
00:16:59,300 --> 00:17:01,300
Get the doctor!

264
00:17:01,300 --> 00:17:03,300
The vet! The chamber hunter!

265
00:17:05,300 --> 00:17:07,300
Ms. Steller, do you have a wish, Mrs. Rottenmeier?

266
00:17:07,300 --> 00:17:09,300
Get rid of this dragon or this...

267
00:17:10,100 --> 00:17:11,700
or whatever it is, out of the house!

268
00:17:11,700 --> 00:17:13,700
As ordered. As Madame wishes.

269
00:17:22,644 --> 00:17:25,644
She could bear that. Well done.

270
00:17:25,644 --> 00:17:27,644
I like your instrument.

271
00:17:27,644 --> 00:17:29,644
I still don't have the 20 pfennigs.

272
00:17:29,644 --> 00:17:31,644
Yes, I know. One moment.

273
00:17:31,644 --> 00:17:33,644
Here, 20 pfennigs for yesterday afternoon,

274
00:17:33,644 --> 00:17:35,644
and for today, because it was especially successful,

275
00:17:35,644 --> 00:17:37,644
another 20.

276
00:17:37,644 --> 00:17:39,644
Thank you.

277
00:17:42,324 --> 00:17:47,324
I'm going to put this very unpleasant matter on the ground after the lesson.

278
00:17:49,324 --> 00:17:52,324
Please, Mr. Candidate, don't let it bother you any further.

279
00:17:52,324 --> 00:17:54,324
The Greeks!

280
00:17:55,324 --> 00:17:57,324
Come in!

281
00:17:59,300 --> 00:18:01,300
Strange.

282
00:18:03,300 --> 00:18:05,300
Come in!

283
00:18:05,300 --> 00:18:10,300
It's very unpleasant that I have to disturb you, but it's something that was
given to you for Mrs. Clara.

284
00:18:10,300 --> 00:18:12,300
I didn't know what we ordered.

285
00:18:14,300 --> 00:18:15,300
I'll take it.

286
00:18:15,300 --> 00:18:17,300
Open it, Mr. Rottenmeier.

287
00:18:17,300 --> 00:18:20,300
Later, child. After school.

288
00:18:20,300 --> 00:18:23,300
First the work, then the pleasure.

289
00:18:23,300 --> 00:18:26,300
Mr. candidate, please don't stop.

290
00:18:26,300 --> 00:18:28,300
Just a moment.

291
00:18:28,892 --> 00:18:30,892
Don't you want to know?

292
00:18:30,892 --> 00:18:31,892
No.

293
00:18:31,892 --> 00:18:33,892
Aren't you curious at all?

294
00:18:33,892 --> 00:18:35,892
Not at all.

295
00:18:35,892 --> 00:18:37,892
I can't understand that.

296
00:18:37,892 --> 00:18:39,892
Mr. candidate, just one look, okay?

297
00:18:39,892 --> 00:18:41,892
That's up to Mrs. Rottenmeier.

298
00:18:41,892 --> 00:18:45,892
Mrs. Rottenmeier, just one look, please.

299
00:18:45,892 --> 00:18:47,892
I said no.

300
00:18:47,892 --> 00:18:51,892
But I'm so curious. I can't continue learning if I don't know what's in the
basket.

301
00:18:51,892 --> 00:18:53,892
And Heidi doesn't either.

302
00:18:53,892 --> 00:18:57,892
Well, it looks like we've distracted the children now.

303
00:18:58,028 --> 00:19:02,428
It seems so. We should allow you to take a look inside the basket.

304
00:19:02,428 --> 00:19:04,428
Do you consider this to be acceptable?

305
00:19:04,428 --> 00:19:09,628
What should you do? You would only take part in the class unnoticed anyway.

306
00:19:09,628 --> 00:19:16,428
It's better to allow you a little break. Show them what's in the basket and
you'll see, the work will be a lot more fun afterwards.

307
00:19:16,428 --> 00:19:19,428
To be honest, I'm also curious.

308
00:19:26,854 --> 00:19:30,854
Maybe it's about fresh fruit, and fruit is always good for the brain.

309
00:19:34,854 --> 00:19:37,854
What's the matter with you, Mr. Candidate? Can't you get out of here?

310
00:19:38,854 --> 00:19:41,854
Is your behavior strange?

311
00:19:42,854 --> 00:19:47,854
Hello, Mrs. Rottenmeier. No excitement. Everything is fine. Cuckoo. Cat.

312
00:19:48,854 --> 00:19:51,854
What? Cat? Alive?

313
00:19:51,854 --> 00:19:56,854
Oh, Sebastian! The shovel!

314
00:19:57,854 --> 00:20:00,854
Help! Help me!

315
00:20:01,854 --> 00:20:04,854
Help me, Sebastian!

316
00:20:08,358 --> 00:20:12,358
Did you know that? Of course you knew that!

317
00:20:12,358 --> 00:20:14,358
Give me one!

318
00:20:27,358 --> 00:20:29,358
Leave my feet alone! Let me kiss!

319
00:20:29,358 --> 00:20:31,358
Sebastian! Sebastian!

320
00:20:31,358 --> 00:20:32,358
Don't!

321
00:20:32,358 --> 00:20:34,358
Sebastian!

322
00:20:34,358 --> 00:20:36,358
I'll kill you!

323
00:20:36,902 --> 00:20:38,902
What are you doing on the table?

324
00:20:38,902 --> 00:20:41,902
Get out of the way, you disgusting cats!

325
00:20:41,902 --> 00:20:43,902
Yes, madam.

326
00:20:43,902 --> 00:20:45,902
Come on, you little...

327
00:20:45,902 --> 00:20:47,902
Come on!

328
00:20:47,902 --> 00:20:49,902
Listen to me!

329
00:20:49,902 --> 00:20:51,902
Help me!

330
00:20:52,934 --> 00:20:54,934
Don't be afraid, my little one!

331
00:21:00,152 --> 00:21:02,152
Miss Rottenmeier, you have complaints.

332
00:21:02,152 --> 00:21:04,152
That was probably too much for the poor.

333
00:21:06,152 --> 00:21:08,152
It was never so funny here.

334
00:21:08,152 --> 00:21:11,152
I'm sorry that the cats are now being brought back.

335
00:21:11,152 --> 00:21:12,152
They were so cute.

336
00:21:12,152 --> 00:21:14,152
After the excitement, it's no wonder.

337
00:21:14,152 --> 00:21:16,152
But I would love to know where they come from.

338
00:21:17,152 --> 00:21:20,152
Mau Mau, we forgot Mau Mau.

339
00:21:20,152 --> 00:21:21,152
I'll get her.

340
00:21:23,152 --> 00:21:24,152
Yours, Madame.

341
00:21:25,152 --> 00:21:28,152
Oh, this child, this child.

342
00:21:30,152 --> 00:21:30,360
Subtitles by Stephanie Geiges

343
00:21:30,360 --> 00:21:33,360
You should lock her up in the cellar for a whole week.

344
00:21:33,360 --> 00:21:36,360
Lock her up at least one afternoon in the cellar.

345
00:21:36,360 --> 00:21:38,360
Then she'll bring the mice up again.

346
00:21:42,360 --> 00:21:44,360
Oh, they're still there!

347
00:21:44,360 --> 00:21:47,360
Everywhere, I can hear them meowing.

348
00:21:47,360 --> 00:21:49,360
They sit in the corner and laugh at me.

349
00:21:49,360 --> 00:21:51,360
But no, I've taken them all away.

350
00:21:51,360 --> 00:21:54,360
And not forgotten? Not forgotten by any chance?

351
00:21:54,360 --> 00:21:55,360
None.

352
00:21:59,256 --> 00:22:04,256
There she is. She ate well. She ate everything we gave her for breakfast.

353
00:22:04,256 --> 00:22:06,256
Give it to me on the lap, Heidi, please.

354
00:22:06,256 --> 00:22:07,256
There!

355
00:22:13,256 --> 00:22:17,256
Mau Mau, do you know what I think? The other cats also came from where you came
from.

356
00:22:17,256 --> 00:22:20,256
So it was Heidi's fault again.

357
00:22:20,256 --> 00:22:22,256
Oh, that tickles!

358
00:22:24,256 --> 00:22:26,256
Miss Rottenmeier!

359
00:22:26,904 --> 00:22:30,904
What do you think, was it Heidi or was it not?

360
00:22:38,904 --> 00:22:40,904
That was an exciting day for the two of them.

361
00:22:40,904 --> 00:22:45,904
First came the turtledove boy with his turtle and then the many little kittens.

362
00:22:45,904 --> 00:22:49,904
Klara could not remember that she had ever laughed like that before.

363
00:22:55,800 --> 00:23:01,800
Heidi and Clara kept their secret that they were hiding in the tower room well.

364
00:23:01,800 --> 00:23:06,800
Still, Mrs. Rottenmeier was not able to find out where this quiet moaning came
from that she heard.

365
00:23:06,800 --> 00:23:11,800
She still firmly believed that her stressed nerves were giving her the moaning.

366
00:23:11,800 --> 00:23:15,800
And every time she took a headache pill when it meowed.

367
00:23:15,800 --> 00:23:18,800
Of course, Clara and Heidi could laugh about it from the heart.

368
00:23:18,800 --> 00:23:21,800
But then it got dangerous all of a sudden.

369
00:23:21,800 --> 00:23:24,174
Mrs. Rottenmeier discovered something.

370
00:23:24,174 --> 00:23:27,674
But we want to tell you about it in our next story.

371
00:23:28,674 --> 00:23:36,174
Heidi, Heidi, your world are the mountains.

372
00:23:36,674 --> 00:23:44,174
Heidi, Heidi, because up here you are at home.

373
00:23:44,674 --> 00:23:50,174
Heidi, Heidi, come home.

374
00:23:50,174 --> 00:23:57,174
Find your happiness, come back home.

